1
00:00:02,294 --> 00:00:05,673
ARCHER: CAPTAIN'S STARLOG,
MARCH 21, 2153.

2
00:00:05,714 --> 00:00:08,550
AFTER THREE DAYS EXPLORING
AN UNINHABITED PLANET,

3
00:00:08,592 --> 00:00:10,093
COMMANDER TUCKER AND I

4
00:00:10,135 --> 00:00:11,887
HAVE BEEN CALLED BACK
TO "ENTERPRISE"

5
00:00:11,929 --> 00:00:13,430
TO GREET AN UNEXPECTED VISITOR.

6
00:00:13,472 --> 00:00:16,016
MAYBE YOU WERE LIGHT-HEADED
FROM THE ALTITUDE.

7
00:00:16,057 --> 00:00:17,559
TUCKER: I DIDN'T SLIP.

8
00:00:17,601 --> 00:00:19,269
THAT OVERHANG GAVE WAY
THE MOMENT I PUT MY FOOT ON IT.

9
00:00:19,311 --> 00:00:20,855
ARCHER: I WALKED ON THE SAME
ROCKS YOU DID.

10
00:00:20,896 --> 00:00:22,481
TUCKER:
WELL, MAYBE YOU LOOSENED THEM.

11
00:00:22,523 --> 00:00:24,316
YOU DO WEIGH A FEW KILOS
MORE THAN I DO.

12
00:00:24,358 --> 00:00:26,360
[DOOR OPENS]

13
00:00:26,401 --> 00:00:28,654
ARCHER: REPORT.

14
00:00:28,696 --> 00:00:31,031
REED: IT DROPPED OUT OF WARP
30 MINUTES AGO

15
00:00:31,072 --> 00:00:33,283
AND THE PILOT SENT
A BRIEF AUDIO MESSAGE.

16
00:00:33,325 --> 00:00:35,828
HE INSISTED ON SPEAKING
WITH YOU RIGHT AWAY.

17
00:00:35,870 --> 00:00:37,913
ARCHER: ANY IDEA WHAT HE WANTS?
REED: HE WOULDN'T SAY.

18
00:00:37,955 --> 00:00:40,123
BUT I DID MANAGE TO
FIND HIS SHIP DESIGN

19
00:00:40,165 --> 00:00:42,501
IN THE VULCAN DATABASE.

20
00:00:42,543 --> 00:00:43,836
IT'S TELLARITE.

21
00:00:43,878 --> 00:00:46,380
ARCHER: T'POL'S MENTIONED THEM.

22
00:00:47,965 --> 00:00:49,508
OPEN A CHANNEL.

23
00:00:51,760 --> 00:00:54,722
THIS IS JONATHAN ARCHER
OF THE "ENTERPRISE."

24
00:00:54,763 --> 00:00:55,973
WHAT CAN I DO FOR YOU?

25
00:00:56,015 --> 00:00:57,474
SKALAAR:<i> YOU CAN START</i>
<i>BY TELLING ME</i>

26
00:00:57,516 --> 00:00:59,226
<i>WHAT YOU'RE DOING HERE.</i>

27
00:00:59,267 --> 00:01:01,520
ARCHER: I DIDN'T GET YOUR NAME.

28
00:01:01,562 --> 00:01:03,146
SKALAAR:<i> CAPTAIN SKALAAR</i>

29
00:01:03,188 --> 00:01:05,524
<i>OF THE TELLARITE</i>
<i>MINING CONSORTIUM.</i>

30
00:01:05,566 --> 00:01:08,736
ARCHER:
WE'RE STUDYING THIS PLANET.

31
00:01:08,777 --> 00:01:11,154
I HAVE THREE SCIENCE TEAMS
ON THE SURFACE.

32
00:01:11,196 --> 00:01:13,615
WE'RE ALSO HERE
FOR A LITTLE SHORE LEAVE.

33
00:01:13,657 --> 00:01:15,325
SKALAAR:<i> SHORE LEAVE?</i>

34
00:01:15,367 --> 00:01:16,911
ARCHER: VACATION.

35
00:01:16,952 --> 00:01:19,038
IT'S BEEN AWHILE SINCE WE'VE HAD
A CHANCE TO RELAX.

36
00:01:19,079 --> 00:01:22,123
SKALAAR:
<i>IN THAT CASE, I RECOMMEND</i>

37
00:01:22,165 --> 00:01:24,251
<i>YOU VISIT THE EQUATORIAL RANGE.</i>

38
00:01:24,292 --> 00:01:28,005
<i>THE VIEW FROM</i>
<i>THE NORTH SUMMIT IS INSPIRING.</i>

39
00:01:28,047 --> 00:01:29,924
ARCHER: YOU'VE BEEN HERE BEFORE?

40
00:01:29,965 --> 00:01:31,508
SKALAAR:<i> MANY TIMES.</i>

41
00:01:31,550 --> 00:01:33,969
<i>I PREFER TO THINK OF IT</i>
<i>AS MY OWN PERSONAL RETREAT.</i>

42
00:01:34,011 --> 00:01:36,221
<i>YOU MUSTN'T LEAVE</i>
<i>UNTIL YOU'VE EXPERIENCED</i>

43
00:01:36,263 --> 00:01:41,184
<i>THE HYDROTHERMAL POOLS</i>
<i>OF REN-GHAM. MMM...</i>

44
00:01:41,226 --> 00:01:42,352
ARCHER: WHERE ARE THEY?

45
00:01:42,394 --> 00:01:43,979
SKALAAR:<i> THE POLAR ISLAND CHAIN,</i>

46
00:01:44,021 --> 00:01:47,357
<i>227 KILOMETERS</i>
<i>FROM THE SOUTHERN TIP</i>

47
00:01:47,399 --> 00:01:49,068
<i>OF THE RYKOS SHORELINE.</i>

48
00:01:49,109 --> 00:01:50,945
<i>LOOK FOR THE PYROCLASTIC</i>
<i>DEBRIS FIELD,</i>

49
00:01:50,986 --> 00:01:52,863
<i>THEN FOLLOW THE LAVA TUBES...</i>

50
00:01:52,905 --> 00:01:54,406
TUCKER: SOUNDS LIKE
WE COULD USE A GUIDE.

51
00:01:54,448 --> 00:01:57,325
SKALAAR:<i> I'D BE HAPPY</i>
<i>TO SHOW YOU.</i>

52
00:01:57,367 --> 00:01:59,286
ARCHER:
SURE WE'RE NOT INTRUDING?

53
00:01:59,327 --> 00:02:00,829
SKALAAR:<i> NOT AT ALL.</i>

54
00:02:00,871 --> 00:02:03,123
<i>I'LL MEET YOU</i>
<i>AT YOUR STARBOARD DOCKING PORT.</i>

55
00:02:03,164 --> 00:02:06,835
<i>I'LL HELP YOU PLAN</i>
<i>YOUR SHORE LEAVE.</i>

56
00:02:08,462 --> 00:02:10,089
ARCHER: T'POL SAYS THEY'RE

57
00:02:10,130 --> 00:02:12,507
NOT THE MOST AGREEABLE SPECIES.

58
00:02:12,549 --> 00:02:15,343
APPARENTLY THEY ENJOY
A GOOD ARGUMENT.

59
00:02:15,385 --> 00:02:18,764
IT'S CONSIDERED A SPORT
ON THEIR PLANET.

60
00:02:18,806 --> 00:02:20,515
TUCKER:
WELL, I'VE GOT AN OLD GIRLFRIEND

61
00:02:20,557 --> 00:02:22,225
THIS GUY MIGHT LIKE TO MEET.

62
00:02:22,267 --> 00:02:24,227
[ARCHER LAUGHS]

63
00:02:45,540 --> 00:02:48,335
SINGER:
♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG ROAD ♪

64
00:02:50,004 --> 00:02:53,132
♪ GETTING FROM THERE TO HERE ♪

65
00:02:53,172 --> 00:02:57,011
♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG TIME ♪

66
00:02:57,052 --> 00:03:00,973
♪ BUT MY TIME IS FINALLY NEAR ♪

67
00:03:01,015 --> 00:03:05,435
♪ AND I WILL SEE MY DREAM
COME ALIVE AT LAST ♪

68
00:03:05,477 --> 00:03:08,814
♪ I WILL TOUCH THE SKY ♪

69
00:03:08,856 --> 00:03:12,734
♪ AND THEY'RE NOT GONNA
HOLD ME DOWN NO MORE ♪

70
00:03:12,776 --> 00:03:15,779
♪ NO, THEY'RE
NOT GONNA CHANGE MY MIND ♪

71
00:03:15,821 --> 00:03:18,699
♪ 'CAUSE I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

72
00:03:18,740 --> 00:03:20,701
♪ OF THE HEART ♪

73
00:03:20,742 --> 00:03:23,912
♪ I'M GOING WHERE MY HEART
WILL TAKE ME ♪

74
00:03:23,954 --> 00:03:28,876
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH TO BELIEVE ♪

75
00:03:28,917 --> 00:03:31,670
♪ I CAN DO ANYTHING ♪

76
00:03:31,712 --> 00:03:36,717
♪ I'VE GOT STRENGTH
OF THE SOUL ♪

77
00:03:36,758 --> 00:03:39,469
♪ AND NO ONE'S GONNA BEND
OR BREAK ME ♪

78
00:03:39,511 --> 00:03:45,017
♪ I CAN REACH ANY STAR ♪

79
00:03:45,059 --> 00:03:46,351
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

80
00:03:46,393 --> 00:03:48,770
♪ I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT ♪

81
00:03:48,812 --> 00:03:53,108
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

82
00:03:53,150 --> 00:03:56,653
♪ FAITH OF THE HEART ♪

83
00:04:07,748 --> 00:04:10,876
[BEEPING]

84
00:04:10,918 --> 00:04:12,836
HOSHI: I'M PICKING UP
WEAPONS FIRE ON "E" DECK.

85
00:04:12,878 --> 00:04:14,337
STARBOARD AIRLOCK.

86
00:04:14,379 --> 00:04:16,131
REED: SEND A SECURITY TEAM.

87
00:04:16,173 --> 00:04:17,883
BRIDGE TO CAPTAIN ARCHER.

88
00:04:20,301 --> 00:04:22,137
TRAVIS: THE TELLARITE SHIP'S
TRYING TO UNDOCK

89
00:04:22,179 --> 00:04:23,722
WITH THE SEALS LOCKED.

90
00:04:23,764 --> 00:04:25,599
REED:
ENGAGE THE EMERGENCY CLAMPS.

91
00:04:32,606 --> 00:04:35,067
TRAVIS: HE'S GOING TO WARP.
REED: PURSUIT COURSE.

92
00:04:37,111 --> 00:04:38,946
TRAVIS: HE'S DISABLED
OUR STARBOARD NACELLE.

93
00:04:38,987 --> 00:04:40,530
WE CAN'T FOLLOW HIM, SIR.

94
00:04:40,572 --> 00:04:42,908
REED: GET THOSE TEAMS UP
FROM THE SURFACE.

95
00:04:52,584 --> 00:04:54,628
TUCKER: We're having trouble
isolating his signature.

96
00:04:54,669 --> 00:04:56,671
He must have done something
to mask it.

97
00:04:56,713 --> 00:04:58,715
T'POL: HOW LONG
UNTIL WE HAVE WARP DRIVE?

98
00:04:58,757 --> 00:05:00,134
TUCKER: LESS THAN AN HOUR.

99
00:05:00,175 --> 00:05:01,760
T'POL: I'm on my way
to the bridge.

100
00:05:01,802 --> 00:05:03,386
TUCKER: ACKNOWLEDGED.

101
00:05:03,428 --> 00:05:05,013
PHLOX: I'M AFRAID
YOU'RE NOT GOING ANYWHERE

102
00:05:05,055 --> 00:05:06,598
FOR THE MOMENT.

103
00:05:06,640 --> 00:05:09,434
WE BROUGHT A STOWAWAY WITH US--
A RATHER UNUSUAL MICROBE.

104
00:05:09,476 --> 00:05:10,936
T'POL: IS IT CONTAGIOUS?

105
00:05:10,978 --> 00:05:12,353
PHLOX: I'LL HAVE TO RUN
SOME MORE TESTS.

106
00:05:12,395 --> 00:05:15,565
TO BE SAFE, WE SHOULD
BOTH GO THROUGH DECON.

107
00:05:47,806 --> 00:05:49,390
ARCHER: WHAT DO YOU WANT?

108
00:05:52,477 --> 00:05:54,479
I ASKED YOU A QUESTION.

109
00:05:54,521 --> 00:05:56,231
AAH!

110
00:05:56,273 --> 00:05:59,943
SKALAAR: I'D STAY CLEAR
OF THOSE EMITTERS IF I WERE YOU.

111
00:05:59,985 --> 00:06:04,114
THE VERY LATEST TECHNOLOGY.
I INSTALLED THEM LAST MONTH.

112
00:06:04,156 --> 00:06:05,824
ARCHER:
I DOUBT THIS SHIP OF YOURS

113
00:06:05,866 --> 00:06:07,868
WILL BE A MATCH
FOR "ENTERPRISE."

114
00:06:07,909 --> 00:06:09,577
SKALAAR: I'VE TAKEN
APPROPRIATE COUNTERMEASURES.

115
00:06:09,619 --> 00:06:12,664
WE WON'T BE SEEING
ANY MORE OF YOUR STARSHIP.

116
00:06:14,124 --> 00:06:16,877
ARCHER: I WANT TO KNOW
WHERE YOU'RE TAKING ME.

117
00:06:20,797 --> 00:06:23,800
MY CREW'S NOT GONNA GIVE UP
UNTIL THEY FIND ME.

118
00:06:24,926 --> 00:06:26,720
IF YOU TAKE ME BACK,

119
00:06:26,761 --> 00:06:28,722
I'D BE WILLING TO FORGET
THIS EVER HAPPENED.

120
00:06:28,763 --> 00:06:30,473
SKALAAR:
YOU CAN EITHER BE QUIET

121
00:06:30,515 --> 00:06:33,060
OR SPEND THE REST
OF THIS TRIP UNCONSCIOUS.

122
00:06:33,101 --> 00:06:35,020
WHICH DO YOU PREFER?

123
00:06:43,737 --> 00:06:45,404
PHLOX: HMM.

124
00:06:45,446 --> 00:06:47,782
THIS MICROBE IS MORE RESILIENT
THAN I THOUGHT.

125
00:06:49,534 --> 00:06:52,329
IT DOESN'T SEEM TO BE VULNERABLE
TO THETA RADIATION.

126
00:06:52,371 --> 00:06:54,622
T'POL: PERHAPS YOU CAN
INCREASE THE DOSAGE.

127
00:06:54,664 --> 00:06:56,083
PHLOX:
THAT WOULDN'T BE ADVISABLE.

128
00:06:56,124 --> 00:06:57,918
WE'D BOTH SUFFER
PERMANENT CELLULAR DAMAGE.

129
00:06:57,959 --> 00:06:59,920
T'POL: THERE MUST BE
SOMETHING ELSE YOU CAN TRY.

130
00:06:59,961 --> 00:07:03,882
PHLOX: DECON GEL "E"
MAY NEUTRALIZE THE MICROBE.

131
00:07:03,924 --> 00:07:06,260
BUT, UH, IT WILL BE
SEVERAL HOURS

132
00:07:06,301 --> 00:07:07,802
BEFORE WE KNOW
IF IT'S EFFECTIVE.

133
00:07:07,844 --> 00:07:10,430
T'POL:
I CAN'T STAY HERE SEVERAL HOURS.

134
00:07:10,471 --> 00:07:12,849
PHLOX: YOU HAVE LITTLE CHOICE.

135
00:07:12,891 --> 00:07:16,103
THIS ORGANISM APPEARS
TO BE INFECTIOUS,

136
00:07:16,144 --> 00:07:18,772
AND HUMANS WOULD BE FAR MORE
VULNERABLE TO IT

137
00:07:18,813 --> 00:07:20,399
THAN YOU OR I.

138
00:07:21,733 --> 00:07:23,318
COMMANDER TUCKER
IS QUITE CAPABLE.

139
00:07:23,360 --> 00:07:25,612
IF HE NEEDS YOUR HELP,
HE KNOWS WHERE TO FIND YOU.

140
00:07:42,629 --> 00:07:45,840
FORTUNATELY, NO ONE ELSE
ON THE SURFACE

141
00:07:45,882 --> 00:07:47,759
WAS EXPOSED TO THE MICROBE.

142
00:07:47,801 --> 00:07:49,719
I SUSPECT YOU AND I
WERE CONTAMINATED

143
00:07:49,761 --> 00:07:53,098
WHEN WE CLIMBED
INTO THE SECOND RAVINE.

144
00:07:53,140 --> 00:07:55,434
CONSIDERING THE QUANTITY
OF FAUNA DOWN THERE,

145
00:07:55,475 --> 00:07:57,518
I'M NOT AT ALL SURPRISED.

146
00:07:57,560 --> 00:07:59,104
WE WERE PROBABLY
INFECTED

147
00:07:59,146 --> 00:08:01,564
BY THE MARSUPIALS I FOUND.

148
00:08:01,606 --> 00:08:03,650
T'POL:
I TOLD YOU TO LEAVE THEM ALONE.

149
00:08:03,691 --> 00:08:07,028
PHLOX: THEIR SALIVA IS
A NATURAL ANTICOAGULANT.

150
00:08:07,070 --> 00:08:10,240
I COULDN'T RETURN
TO THE SHIP WITHOUT A SAMPLE.

151
00:08:16,913 --> 00:08:19,374
I COULD USE YOUR ASSISTANCE.

152
00:08:28,049 --> 00:08:29,926
T'POL: I WASN'T AWARE
A CURTAIN WAS INSTALLED.

153
00:08:29,968 --> 00:08:31,761
PHLOX:
NOT EVERYONE IS COMFORTABLE

154
00:08:31,803 --> 00:08:34,264
WITH THE IDEA OF DISROBING
IN FRONT OF OTHERS.

155
00:08:34,306 --> 00:08:36,599
T'POL:
AN ODD ATTITUDE FOR A PHYSICIAN.

156
00:08:36,641 --> 00:08:38,935
PHLOX: IT'S A CHARACTERISTIC
OF DENOBULAN MALES.

157
00:08:38,977 --> 00:08:41,521
WE'RE MORE INHIBITED
THAN OUR WOMEN.

158
00:08:41,562 --> 00:08:45,275
IT'S, UH, WELL, LED TO A NUMBER
OF AWKWARD MOMENTS.

159
00:08:45,317 --> 00:08:48,195
MY STARFLEET PHYSICAL
WAS AN EXPERIENCE

160
00:08:48,236 --> 00:08:50,780
I NEVER HOPE TO REPEAT.

161
00:09:00,374 --> 00:09:02,209
T'POL: IF YOU WOULDN'T MIND.

162
00:09:12,927 --> 00:09:14,054
[BEEPING]

163
00:09:14,095 --> 00:09:15,555
REED: THE SENSORS
ARE PICKING UP

164
00:09:15,596 --> 00:09:17,015
A FAINT WARP SIGNATURE.

165
00:09:17,057 --> 00:09:18,725
TUCKER:
CAN YOU GET A FIX ON IT?

166
00:09:18,766 --> 00:09:21,353
REED: BEARING 071 MARK 32.

167
00:09:21,395 --> 00:09:24,772
IT'S ERRATIC, BUT IT MATCHES
OUR TELLARITE FRIEND.

168
00:09:24,814 --> 00:09:26,400
TUCKER: SET A COURSE.

169
00:09:26,441 --> 00:09:28,485
MAXIMUM WARP.

170
00:09:33,156 --> 00:09:34,991
KLINGON: You're speaking
on a secure channel.

171
00:09:35,033 --> 00:09:37,285
SKALAAR: I'M TRYING
TO REACH CAPTAIN GOROTH.

172
00:09:37,327 --> 00:09:39,787
IT'S VERY IMPORTANT
THAT I SPEAK WITH HIM.

173
00:09:39,829 --> 00:09:41,540
KLINGON: We're attempting
to transfer you.

174
00:09:41,581 --> 00:09:42,832
Stand by.

175
00:09:42,874 --> 00:09:45,752
GOROTH: This is Goroth.
What do you want?

176
00:09:45,793 --> 00:09:47,712
SKALAAR: I HAVE THE FUGITIVE.

177
00:09:47,754 --> 00:09:50,590
GOROTH: He's in your custody?

178
00:09:50,631 --> 00:09:53,343
SKALAAR: HE'S STANDING ABOUT
FIVE METERS FROM ME.

179
00:09:53,385 --> 00:09:55,762
YOU'LL BE PLEASED TO KNOW
HE'S STILL ALIVE.

180
00:09:55,803 --> 00:09:58,306
I'M BRINGING HIM
TO KRONOS AS WE AGREED.

181
00:09:58,348 --> 00:09:59,682
GOROTH: No.

182
00:09:59,724 --> 00:10:01,893
I'm transmitting
rendezvous coordinates.

183
00:10:01,935 --> 00:10:03,395
Be there in two days.

184
00:10:03,437 --> 00:10:06,064
SKALAAR: I TRUST YOU'LL HAVE
THE FULL PAYMENT.

185
00:10:06,106 --> 00:10:08,108
GOROTH:
You'll get what was promised.

186
00:10:08,149 --> 00:10:10,860
SKALAAR: PLEASURE DOING BUSINESS
WITH YOU, CAPTAIN.

187
00:10:12,112 --> 00:10:13,947
AS ALWAYS.

188
00:10:13,988 --> 00:10:15,823
ARCHER:
HOW MUCH ARE THEY PAYING YOU?

189
00:10:18,368 --> 00:10:21,788
YOU MENTIONED
THE KLINGON HOMEWORLD, KRONOS.

190
00:10:23,498 --> 00:10:25,500
I ASSUME THIS HAS
SOMETHING TO DO

191
00:10:25,542 --> 00:10:27,252
WITH MY ESCAPING PRISON.

192
00:10:30,713 --> 00:10:32,882
YOU DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHAT I'M ACCUSED OF.

193
00:10:32,924 --> 00:10:34,842
SKALAAR: YOU'RE RIGHT.

194
00:10:34,884 --> 00:10:37,095
AND I DON'T CARE TO.

195
00:10:52,152 --> 00:10:53,945
REED:
THE SIGNATURE'S HOLDING STEADY.

196
00:10:53,987 --> 00:10:55,822
LOOKS LIKE HE'S ORBITING
A G-TYPE STAR.

197
00:10:55,863 --> 00:10:58,074
TUCKER: GO TO TACTICAL ALERT.

198
00:11:02,662 --> 00:11:04,789
REED: IT APPEARS TO BE
A BEACON OF SOME KIND.

199
00:11:04,831 --> 00:11:06,291
IT'S GENERATING A WARP SIGNATURE

200
00:11:06,333 --> 00:11:07,834
IDENTICAL TO THE TELLARITE'S.

201
00:11:07,875 --> 00:11:11,254
TUCKER: A DECOY.
ANYTHING ON SENSORS?

202
00:11:12,506 --> 00:11:14,882
WE'RE GONNA
HAVE TO START ALL OVER.

203
00:11:14,924 --> 00:11:16,510
REED: WE'RE GETTING
TOO MUCH INTERFERENCE

204
00:11:16,551 --> 00:11:18,094
FROM THAT DEVICE.

205
00:11:18,136 --> 00:11:19,638
IT'S THROWING OFF OUR SCANS.

206
00:11:19,678 --> 00:11:21,181
TUCKER: THEN GET RID OF IT.

207
00:11:21,222 --> 00:11:23,808
REED: WITH PLEASURE, SIR.

208
00:11:32,442 --> 00:11:35,529
ARCHER: I HAVE NO IDEA WHAT
THE KLINGONS ARE PAYING YOU.

209
00:11:35,570 --> 00:11:39,407
BUT WHATEVER IT IS,
STARFLEET WILL DOUBLE IT.

210
00:11:39,449 --> 00:11:41,368
SKALAAR: I DON'T TAKE BRIBES
FROM CRIMINALS.

211
00:11:41,409 --> 00:11:43,244
ARCHER: I'M NOT A CRIMINAL.

212
00:11:43,286 --> 00:11:45,539
SKALAAR: KLINGON JUDICIARY
SAYS THAT YOU ARE.

213
00:11:45,580 --> 00:11:49,376
ARCHER: MY CRIME WAS HELPING
A SHIP FULL OF REFUGEES.

214
00:11:49,417 --> 00:11:52,420
SKALAAR: WELL, THAT WAS
VERY NOBLE OF YOU.

215
00:11:52,462 --> 00:11:54,589
YOU'LL THINK TWICE
BEFORE DOING THAT AGAIN.

216
00:11:54,631 --> 00:11:56,550
[SKALAAR CHUCKLES]

217
00:11:56,591 --> 00:11:58,009
ARCHER: IT'S PRETTY CLEAR

218
00:11:58,051 --> 00:12:01,054
I'M NEVER GOING
TO GET THE CHANCE.

219
00:12:01,095 --> 00:12:06,434
I WAS SENTENCED TO LIFE
IN PRISON ON RURA PENTHE.

220
00:12:06,476 --> 00:12:08,436
EVER HEARD OF IT?

221
00:12:08,478 --> 00:12:10,313
SKALAAR:
I'M FAMILIAR WITH RURA PENTHE.

222
00:12:10,355 --> 00:12:11,772
ARCHER: THE MAGISTRATE

223
00:12:11,814 --> 00:12:15,109
ISN'T GOING
TO BE SO LENIENT NEXT TIME.

224
00:12:17,278 --> 00:12:19,364
I'LL PROBABLY BE EXECUTED.

225
00:12:22,200 --> 00:12:23,868
SKALAAR: THAT'S NOT MY CONCERN.

226
00:12:23,910 --> 00:12:25,495
ARCHER: YOU DON'T CARE
THAT YOU'RE SENDING

227
00:12:25,537 --> 00:12:27,163
AN INNOCENT MAN TO HIS DEATH?

228
00:12:27,205 --> 00:12:29,249
SKALAAR: I'VE CAPTURED DOZENS
OF FUGITIVES.

229
00:12:29,290 --> 00:12:32,793
EVERY ONE OF THEM CLAIMED
TO BE AN INNOCENT MAN.

230
00:12:32,835 --> 00:12:35,672
ARCHER: IF THE KLINGONS
WANTED THEM, THEY PROBABLY WERE.

231
00:12:37,048 --> 00:12:39,008
YOU DON'T HAVE TO DO THIS!

232
00:12:39,050 --> 00:12:41,595
SKALAAR: GOROTH ALREADY KNOWS
YOU'RE ABOARD.

233
00:12:41,636 --> 00:12:43,221
IF I DON'T DELIVER YOU,

234
00:12:43,263 --> 00:12:47,183
HE'LL OFFER A REWARD
FOR BOTH OF US.

235
00:12:47,225 --> 00:12:49,936
I'VE LEARNED
NEVER TO CROSS A KLINGON.

236
00:12:52,897 --> 00:12:55,024
ARCHER:
IT MUST BE DIFFICULT...

237
00:12:56,317 --> 00:12:58,570
WORKING FOR PEOPLE LIKE THEM.

238
00:12:58,612 --> 00:13:00,280
SKALAAR: I DON'T ANSWER
TO THOSE SAVAGES.

239
00:13:00,321 --> 00:13:02,949
I WORK FOR MYSELF.

240
00:13:02,990 --> 00:13:05,910
ARCHER: THAT'S NOT HOW IT LOOKS
FROM IN HERE.

241
00:13:08,996 --> 00:13:11,291
SKALAAR: IF YOU KNEW
HOW MUCH THEY WERE PAYING ME,

242
00:13:11,332 --> 00:13:13,334
YOU'D UNDERSTAND.

243
00:13:13,376 --> 00:13:16,963
THIS HAS NOTHING TO DO WITH YOU.

244
00:13:17,004 --> 00:13:20,133
I'M SURE YOU'RE NOT
A BAD PERSON.

245
00:13:20,174 --> 00:13:22,135
JUST AN UNLUCKY ONE.

246
00:13:35,315 --> 00:13:37,734
[DEVICE WHIRRING]

247
00:13:42,739 --> 00:13:46,075
T'POL: YOU ARE MAKING IT
DIFFICULT TO MEDITATE.

248
00:13:46,117 --> 00:13:48,620
PHLOX: YOU'VE DEVELOPED
A SLIGHT FEVER.

249
00:13:48,662 --> 00:13:51,289
AND I'M ALSO READING
ELEVATED DOPAMINE LEVELS.

250
00:13:51,331 --> 00:13:53,750
THE MICROBE MAY BE AFFECTING
YOUR LIMBIC SYSTEM.

251
00:13:53,792 --> 00:13:57,295
T'POL: I CAN'T CONCENTRATE
UNDER THESE CONDITIONS.

252
00:13:57,337 --> 00:13:59,880
PHLOX:
I DON'T MEAN TO BE INTRUSIVE.

253
00:13:59,922 --> 00:14:02,133
T'POL:
THE CAPTAIN'S BEEN ABDUCTED.

254
00:14:02,175 --> 00:14:05,136
HE MAY EVEN BE DEAD.

255
00:14:05,178 --> 00:14:06,845
MY PLACE IS ON THE BRIDGE.

256
00:14:06,887 --> 00:14:08,682
PHLOX: SUB-COMMANDER.

257
00:14:11,184 --> 00:14:13,019
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

258
00:14:13,060 --> 00:14:14,895
[T'POL BREATHING HEAVILY]

259
00:14:14,937 --> 00:14:16,063
T'POL: OPEN IT!

260
00:14:16,105 --> 00:14:17,940
PHLOX:
YOU'LL SPREAD THE INFECTION.

261
00:14:17,982 --> 00:14:19,317
T'POL: I'LL GO TO MY QUARTERS!

262
00:14:19,359 --> 00:14:21,361
IF I SEAL OFF
THE VENTILATION SYSTEM,

263
00:14:21,402 --> 00:14:24,364
IT SHOULD MINIMIZE
THE RISK OF EXPOSING ANYONE.

264
00:14:24,405 --> 00:14:26,157
PHLOX:
YOUR QUARTERS ARE ON "C" DECK.

265
00:14:26,199 --> 00:14:27,534
BY THE TIME YOU REACH THEM,

266
00:14:27,575 --> 00:14:29,536
YOU'LL CONTAMINATE
HALF THE SHIP.

267
00:14:29,577 --> 00:14:31,412
T'POL: UNLOCK THIS DOOR.

268
00:14:34,081 --> 00:14:36,876
I GAVE YOU A DIRECT ORDER.

269
00:14:36,917 --> 00:14:38,545
PHLOX:
I'M SORRY, BUT I CAN'T OBEY IT.

270
00:14:38,586 --> 00:14:40,588
T'POL:
I CAN HAVE YOU COURT-MARTIALED.

271
00:14:40,630 --> 00:14:43,341
PHLOX: I DOUBT THAT VERY MU--
T'POL: OPEN IT!

272
00:14:52,099 --> 00:14:53,685
I APOLOGIZE.

273
00:14:55,061 --> 00:15:00,024
I AM HAVING TROUBLE
SUPPRESSING MY EMOTIONS.

274
00:15:00,066 --> 00:15:01,735
PHLOX: WE'LL KNOW IN A FEW HOURS

275
00:15:01,776 --> 00:15:03,403
WHETHER THE GEL IS WORKING.

276
00:15:03,444 --> 00:15:06,030
UNTIL THEN

277
00:15:06,072 --> 00:15:09,784
PERHAPS A MILD SEDATIVE
MAY HELP.

278
00:15:14,163 --> 00:15:16,875
SKALAAR: THE KLINGONS
ARE PAYING 9,000 DARSEKS.

279
00:15:16,916 --> 00:15:19,293
THAT'S MORE THAN ENOUGH
TO GET "TEZRA" BACK.

280
00:15:19,335 --> 00:15:21,713
GAAVRIN:
<i>YOU'RE NOT BEING REALISTIC.</i>

281
00:15:21,755 --> 00:15:23,923
SKALAAR: I ALREADY
HAVE THE HUMAN IN CUSTODY.

282
00:15:23,964 --> 00:15:25,592
THE REWARD IS GUARANTEED.

283
00:15:25,633 --> 00:15:27,635
GAAVRIN:<i> YOU'VE MADE</i>
<i>THIS PROMISE BEFORE.</i>

284
00:15:27,677 --> 00:15:31,598
SKALAAR: IN TWO DAYS, YOU'LL SEE
I'M TELLING THE TRUTH.

285
00:15:31,639 --> 00:15:33,600
GAAVRIN:<i> EVEN IF YOU GET</i>
<i>THE MONEY, WHICH I DOUBT,</i>

286
00:15:33,641 --> 00:15:36,143
<i>IT WOULDN'T CHANGE MY DECISION.</i>

287
00:15:36,185 --> 00:15:37,854
SKALAAR: DO YOU WANT TO SCRUB
PLASMA INJECTORS

288
00:15:37,896 --> 00:15:39,021
THE REST OF YOUR LIFE?

289
00:15:39,063 --> 00:15:41,816
I'M GIVING YOU A CHANCE TO...

290
00:15:41,858 --> 00:15:43,526
OHH!

291
00:15:48,030 --> 00:15:49,407
ARCHER: WHO'S TEZRA?

292
00:15:49,449 --> 00:15:51,451
SKALAAR: "TEZRA'S" NOT A PERSON.

293
00:15:51,492 --> 00:15:54,370
IT'S A CARGO SHIP.

294
00:15:54,412 --> 00:15:56,664
FAR MORE IMPRESSIVE
THAN THIS ANTIQUE.

295
00:15:56,706 --> 00:15:59,333
YOU'RE GOING TO USE THE REWARD
TO BUY YOUR SHIP BACK?

296
00:15:59,375 --> 00:16:01,419
SKALAAR:
YOU'D BE WISE TO KEEP QUIET.

297
00:16:01,461 --> 00:16:03,212
THE KLINGONS PAY ME THE SAME

298
00:16:03,254 --> 00:16:05,172
WHETHER YOU'RE ALIVE OR DEAD.

299
00:16:07,049 --> 00:16:08,468
[BEEPING]

300
00:16:08,509 --> 00:16:10,136
A VESSEL'S APPROACHING.

301
00:16:10,177 --> 00:16:14,766
I WOULDN'T GET TOO OPTIMISTIC.
IT'S NOT YOUR STARSHIP.

302
00:16:21,188 --> 00:16:23,608
KAGO-DARR:
<i>YOU HAVE SOMETHING I WANT.</i>

303
00:16:23,650 --> 00:16:26,402
SKALAAR: ALWAYS ONE STEP
BEHIND ME, EH, KAGO?

304
00:16:26,444 --> 00:16:30,364
KAGO-DARR:<i> DROP OUT OF WARP</i>
<i>AND SURRENDER THE PRISONER.</i>

305
00:16:30,406 --> 00:16:31,866
SKALAAR: WHY WOULD I DO THAT?

306
00:16:31,908 --> 00:16:34,160
KAGO-DARR:
<i>DON'T FORCE ME TO TAKE ACTION.</i>

307
00:16:34,201 --> 00:16:37,664
SKALAAR: GOROTH TOLD YOU
WHERE I WAS, DIDN'T HE?

308
00:16:37,705 --> 00:16:40,374
KAGO-DARR:<i> YOU HAD TWO MONTHS</i>
<i>TO FIND THE HUMAN.</i>

309
00:16:40,416 --> 00:16:42,042
<i>GOROTH CONTACTED ME</i>

310
00:16:42,084 --> 00:16:45,212
<i>BECAUSE YOU OBVIOUSLY</i>
<i>WEREN'T GOING TO SUCCEED.</i>

311
00:16:45,254 --> 00:16:47,131
<i>YOU'RE INCOMPETENT!</i>

312
00:16:47,173 --> 00:16:48,883
SKALAAR: IF I WAS INCOMPETENT,

313
00:16:48,925 --> 00:16:51,260
ARCHER WOULD BE ABOARD
YOUR SHIP, WOULDN'T HE?

314
00:16:51,302 --> 00:16:53,680
KAGO-DARR:<i> THE HUMAN...</i>

315
00:16:53,721 --> 00:16:55,181
<i>NOW.</i>

316
00:16:55,222 --> 00:16:57,767
SKALAAR: OR WHAT?
YOU'LL DESTROY MY SHUTTLE?

317
00:16:57,809 --> 00:17:01,312
CAN'T COLLECT ON ARCHER
IF HE'S A CLOUD OF VAPOR.

318
00:17:01,354 --> 00:17:04,231
YOU MAY WANT TO HOLD ON
TO SOMETHING.

319
00:17:18,830 --> 00:17:20,456
ARCHER: LET ME OUT.
I CAN HELP YOU.

320
00:17:20,498 --> 00:17:22,500
SKALAAR:
YOU MUST THINK I'M A FOOL.

321
00:17:24,878 --> 00:17:26,462
ARCHER: YOU CAN'T
MANEUVER THE SHIP

322
00:17:26,504 --> 00:17:28,589
AND MAKE REPAIRS
AT THE SAME TIME.

323
00:17:30,008 --> 00:17:32,343
I'M A PILOT!
LET ME TAKE THE HELM.

324
00:17:34,971 --> 00:17:37,264
SKALAAR: IF YOU TRY TO ESCAPE...

325
00:17:47,692 --> 00:17:49,569
THIS IS
THE WARP-FIELD REGULATOR,

326
00:17:49,610 --> 00:17:51,320
THE IMPULSE THROTTLE.

327
00:17:51,362 --> 00:17:52,947
ARCHER: NAVIGATION SENSORS?

328
00:17:52,989 --> 00:17:54,323
SKALAAR: THERE.

329
00:17:56,826 --> 00:17:58,745
THERE'S AN L-CLASS PLANET
IN THIS SYSTEM.

330
00:17:58,786 --> 00:18:00,371
I'M TAKING US OUT OF WARP.

331
00:18:00,413 --> 00:18:01,748
SKALAAR: WHAT?

332
00:18:01,789 --> 00:18:03,249
ARCHER: WE CAN'T OUTRUN HIM,

333
00:18:03,290 --> 00:18:04,959
BUT HE MAY NOT BE
ABLE TO NAVIGATE

334
00:18:05,001 --> 00:18:07,086
AS WELL AS WE CAN
IN THE PLANET'S ATMOSPHERE.

335
00:18:16,721 --> 00:18:18,305
SKALAAR:
THIS SHIP WASN'T DESIGNED

336
00:18:18,347 --> 00:18:20,058
FOR THESE MANEUVERS.

337
00:18:22,977 --> 00:18:24,604
WE'VE LOST THE AFT CANNONS.

338
00:18:24,645 --> 00:18:26,230
ARCHER:
WHAT ABOUT FORWARD CANNONS?

339
00:18:26,272 --> 00:18:28,066
SKALAAR: STILL ONLINE.

340
00:18:29,650 --> 00:18:31,277
ARCHER: WHAT ARE THESE?

341
00:18:31,318 --> 00:18:33,153
SKALAAR: SUBSPACE BEACONS.

342
00:18:33,195 --> 00:18:35,489
THEY GENERATE
A FALSE WARP SIGNATURE.

343
00:18:35,531 --> 00:18:37,784
I USED ONE OF THEM
TO EVADE YOUR VESSEL.

344
00:18:37,825 --> 00:18:39,285
ARCHER: GET READY
TO LAUNCH THEM.

345
00:18:39,326 --> 00:18:40,828
SKALAAR: WHAT GOOD WILL THAT DO?

346
00:18:40,870 --> 00:18:42,789
ARCHER: HE'S FLYING ON SENSORS
JUST LIKE WE ARE.

347
00:18:42,830 --> 00:18:46,793
HE'LL ONLY HAVE A 1 IN 3 CHANCE
OF TARGETING US.

348
00:18:46,834 --> 00:18:48,002
SKALAAR: READY.

349
00:18:48,044 --> 00:18:50,088
ARCHER: NOW.

350
00:19:06,938 --> 00:19:09,231
WE KNOCKED OUT HIS ENGINE.

351
00:19:09,273 --> 00:19:11,191
HE'S MAKING
AN EMERGENCY LANDING.

352
00:19:11,233 --> 00:19:13,945
SKALAAR: DON'T CELEBRATE YET.
OUR REACTOR'S LEAKING.

353
00:19:13,987 --> 00:19:15,529
THE WARP DRIVE'S OFF-LINE.

354
00:19:15,571 --> 00:19:18,992
I'M NEVER GOING TO MAKE
THE RENDEZVOUS.

355
00:19:19,033 --> 00:19:20,785
ARCHER: ISN'T THAT A SHAME?

356
00:19:20,827 --> 00:19:23,537
SKALAAR: THE REACTOR
ALSO POWERS LIFE SUPPORT.

357
00:19:23,579 --> 00:19:25,581
ARCHER:
THEN YOU'D BETTER GET TO WORK.

358
00:19:25,623 --> 00:19:29,209
SKALAAR: IT CAN ONLY BE
ACCESSED FROM THE OUTER HULL.

359
00:19:29,251 --> 00:19:30,753
ARCHER:
THEN WE SHOULD SET DOWN HERE.

360
00:19:30,795 --> 00:19:32,964
SKALAAR:
BUT KAGO'S ON THE SURFACE.

361
00:19:33,006 --> 00:19:35,716
ARCHER: WE'LL LAND
A THOUSAND KILOMETERS AWAY.

362
00:19:45,559 --> 00:19:47,227
PHLOX: WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

363
00:19:47,269 --> 00:19:51,065
T'POL: YOU SAID WE'D NEED
ANOTHER TREATMENT.

364
00:19:51,107 --> 00:19:52,608
PHLOX: NOT FOR THREE HOURS.

365
00:19:52,650 --> 00:19:54,527
T'POL: IS THERE ANY HARM
IN STARTING NOW?

366
00:19:54,568 --> 00:19:56,904
PHLOX: I CAN APPLY IT MYSELF.

367
00:19:56,946 --> 00:19:58,572
THANK YOU.

368
00:19:59,866 --> 00:20:01,742
PERHAPS YOU NEED
ANOTHER SEDATIVE.

369
00:20:01,784 --> 00:20:03,285
T'POL: REST IS NOT WHAT I NEED.

370
00:20:03,327 --> 00:20:04,954
PHLOX: SUB-COMMANDER,
THIS BEHAVIOR

371
00:20:04,996 --> 00:20:06,372
IS HARDLY APPROPRIATE.

372
00:20:06,413 --> 00:20:08,457
T'POL: MY NAME IS T'POL.

373
00:20:08,499 --> 00:20:10,043
YOU DON'T FIND ME ATTRACTIVE?

374
00:20:10,084 --> 00:20:12,920
PHLOX: OF COURSE I DO,
BUT THAT IS NOT THE ISSUE.

375
00:20:12,962 --> 00:20:16,298
T'POL: I'M FAMILIAR WITH
DENOBULAN SEXUALITY.

376
00:20:16,340 --> 00:20:18,384
I KNOW THAT YOUR MARRIAGES
AREN'T EXCLUSIVE.

377
00:20:18,425 --> 00:20:20,553
PHLOX: YOU AND I ARE COLLEAGUES.

378
00:20:20,594 --> 00:20:22,221
IT'S AGAINST REGULATIONS.

379
00:20:22,262 --> 00:20:23,848
T'POL: STARFLEET REGULATIONS.

380
00:20:23,890 --> 00:20:26,642
THERE'S NO REASON TO BE
RESTRAINED BY HUMAN MORALITY.

381
00:20:26,684 --> 00:20:29,687
PHLOX: IT'S OBVIOUS
YOU'RE NOT WELL. PLEASE.

382
00:20:32,023 --> 00:20:35,526
T'POL: YOU HAVE NO IDEA
WHAT YOU'RE DENYING YOURSELF.

383
00:20:35,568 --> 00:20:37,319
YOUR ENDORPHIN
AND HORMONAL LEVELS

384
00:20:37,361 --> 00:20:39,072
ARE DANGEROUSLY HIGH.

385
00:20:39,113 --> 00:20:41,115
T'POL: YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND.
I'M NOT ILL.

386
00:20:41,157 --> 00:20:42,950
PHLOX: THESE ARE HARDLY
NORMAL READINGS.

387
00:20:42,992 --> 00:20:46,037
T'POL: THEY'RE NORMAL
FOR A VULCAN IN MY CONDITION.

388
00:20:46,079 --> 00:20:48,039
PHLOX:
YOU KNOW WHAT'S WRONG WITH YOU?

389
00:20:50,083 --> 00:20:52,752
T'POL: IT'S NOT SOMETHING
WE DISCUSS WITH OTHERS.

390
00:20:54,962 --> 00:20:56,547
PHLOX: I BELIEVE IT'S TIME

391
00:20:56,589 --> 00:20:59,092
FOR YOU TO AMEND THAT POLICY.

392
00:20:59,133 --> 00:21:01,928
YOU HAVE MY ASSURANCE
IT WILL REMAIN BETWEEN US.

393
00:21:04,597 --> 00:21:06,807
T'POL: WE CALL IT THE PON FARR--

394
00:21:06,849 --> 00:21:09,018
THE CYCLE OF MATING.

395
00:21:10,603 --> 00:21:13,480
PHLOX: HAVE YOU GONE
THROUGH THIS BEFORE?

396
00:21:15,315 --> 00:21:16,859
T'POL: IT'S NOT TIME.

397
00:21:16,901 --> 00:21:18,569
PHLOX:
IT'S POSSIBLE THE INFECTION

398
00:21:18,611 --> 00:21:20,029
ACTED AS A CATALYST.

399
00:21:20,071 --> 00:21:22,364
T'POL:
WHAT CAUSED IT DOESN'T MATTER.

400
00:21:22,406 --> 00:21:24,867
IF I DON'T MATE WITH A MALE--
VULCAN OR OTHERWISE--

401
00:21:24,909 --> 00:21:26,869
I'LL DIE.

402
00:21:37,171 --> 00:21:41,508
ARCHER: THAT SHIP YOU MENTIONED,
THE "TEZRA"...

403
00:21:41,550 --> 00:21:43,427
SOUNDS PRETTY IMPORTANT TO YOU.

404
00:21:43,469 --> 00:21:45,679
SKALAAR: MORE THAN YOU KNOW.

405
00:21:45,721 --> 00:21:48,390
IF KAGO COLLECTS THE REWARD,

406
00:21:48,432 --> 00:21:53,020
HE'LL PROBABLY WASTE IT
ON ORION SLAVE GIRLS.

407
00:21:53,062 --> 00:21:54,647
NOT ME.

408
00:21:54,688 --> 00:21:57,066
I'M GOING TO DO SOMETHING USEFUL
WITH IT.

409
00:21:57,108 --> 00:21:59,735
ARCHER: I DON'T UNDERSTAND
WHY YOU WANT A CARGO SHIP.

410
00:21:59,777 --> 00:22:02,321
DOESN'T SEEM PRACTICAL
IN YOUR LINE OF WORK.

411
00:22:02,362 --> 00:22:04,157
SKALAAR: YOU THINK
I'VE BEEN CHASING

412
00:22:04,198 --> 00:22:06,826
FUGITIVES MY ENTIRE LIFE?

413
00:22:06,867 --> 00:22:08,953
NO, ONCE I GET THE MONEY,

414
00:22:08,995 --> 00:22:12,581
I'LL HAVE ENOUGH TO PAY OFF
THE IMPOUND FEES.

415
00:22:12,623 --> 00:22:15,001
I'LL BE A FREIGHTER CAPTAIN
AGAIN.

416
00:22:15,042 --> 00:22:17,377
ARCHER:
MY HELMSMAN USED TO RUN FREIGHT.

417
00:22:17,419 --> 00:22:19,046
THE TWO OF YOU
WOULD PROBABLY HAVE

418
00:22:19,088 --> 00:22:20,756
A LOT TO TALK ABOUT.

419
00:22:20,798 --> 00:22:23,383
SKALAAR: NO, THE "TEZRA"
ISN'T LIKE ANY OTHER CARGO SHIP.

420
00:22:23,425 --> 00:22:28,181
SHE WAS THE FIRST OF HER CLASS,
THE FASTEST EVER BUILT.

421
00:22:28,222 --> 00:22:30,348
NOW, SHE COULD HAUL
A MILLION METRIC TONS

422
00:22:30,390 --> 00:22:31,976
AT WARP 4.5.

423
00:22:32,018 --> 00:22:34,478
EVEN YOUR STARSHIP
ISN'T CAPABLE OF THAT.

424
00:22:34,520 --> 00:22:36,856
I RETROFITTED
HER ENGINES MYSELF.

425
00:22:36,897 --> 00:22:40,276
ARCHER: YOU NEVER TOLD ME
WHY IT WAS IMPOUNDED.

426
00:22:40,318 --> 00:22:42,111
SKALAAR:
MY BROTHER AND I WERE HAULING

427
00:22:42,153 --> 00:22:44,155
A SHIPMENT OF FIRE SALT.

428
00:22:45,865 --> 00:22:48,784
I THOUGHT I COULD TRIM
2 OR 3 DAYS OFF OUR JOURNEY

429
00:22:48,826 --> 00:22:51,453
BY CUTTING ACROSS
THE MOST INSIGNIFICANT CORNER

430
00:22:51,495 --> 00:22:53,580
OF KLINGON SPACE.

431
00:22:53,622 --> 00:22:56,125
I LEARNED VERY QUICKLY
THERE'S NO SUCH THING

432
00:22:56,167 --> 00:22:59,212
AS AN INSIGNIFICANT CORNER
OF KLINGON SPACE.

433
00:22:59,253 --> 00:23:02,589
WE WERE LUCKY TO ESCAPE
WITH OUR LIVES,

434
00:23:02,631 --> 00:23:05,259
THOUGH WE DID PAY A PRICE.

435
00:23:05,301 --> 00:23:06,969
ARCHER: THEY TOOK YOUR SHIP.

436
00:23:07,011 --> 00:23:08,846
SKALAAR: AND ITS CARGO, TOO.

437
00:23:08,888 --> 00:23:11,140
MY BROTHER NEVER FORGAVE ME.

438
00:23:11,182 --> 00:23:12,599
I'VE BEEN TRYING TO FIND A WAY

439
00:23:12,641 --> 00:23:14,560
TO GET THE "TEZRA" BACK
EVER SINCE.

440
00:23:14,601 --> 00:23:16,520
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?!

441
00:23:20,024 --> 00:23:22,860
ARCHER: DID YOU REALLY THINK
I WANTED THIS ENGINE FIXED?

442
00:23:22,902 --> 00:23:25,071
YOU'RE TAKING ME TO BE EXECUTED.

443
00:23:33,746 --> 00:23:37,791
SKALAAR: DON'T WORRY.
WE'LL MEET GOROTH ON TIME.

444
00:23:49,053 --> 00:23:51,055
PHLOX: FEELING ANY BETTER?

445
00:23:54,725 --> 00:23:57,561
T'POL: I'M HUNGRY.

446
00:23:57,603 --> 00:24:00,147
PHLOX: OUR MEALS
WILL BE HERE SOON.

447
00:24:00,189 --> 00:24:02,400
T'POL: I WASN'T REFERRING
TO FOOD.

448
00:24:03,901 --> 00:24:05,986
PHLOX:
I'M WORKING AS QUICKLY AS I CAN.

449
00:24:06,028 --> 00:24:09,447
THIS SERUM SHOULD HELP ALLEVIATE
MOST OF YOUR SYMPTOMS.

450
00:24:11,325 --> 00:24:14,287
T'POL:
THERE'S A FAR SIMPLER TREATMENT.

451
00:24:14,328 --> 00:24:15,955
PHLOX: I'D PREFER TO EXPLORE

452
00:24:15,996 --> 00:24:17,831
A MORE CONVENTIONAL APPROACH.

453
00:24:19,708 --> 00:24:22,544
T'POL: YOU HAVE THE CURE.

454
00:24:22,586 --> 00:24:24,964
IT'S UNETHICAL FOR YOU
TO WITHHOLD IT, DOCTOR.

455
00:24:25,005 --> 00:24:26,506
PHLOX: THIS MATING
CYCLE OF YOURS WAS

456
00:24:26,548 --> 00:24:28,175
ARTIFICIALLY INDUCED.

457
00:24:28,217 --> 00:24:30,344
WE CAN'T BE CERTAIN THAT A--

458
00:24:30,386 --> 00:24:31,887
PHYSICAL ENCOUNTER WOULD HELP.

459
00:24:31,929 --> 00:24:33,471
T'POL: I'M WILLING TO TRY.

460
00:24:33,513 --> 00:24:36,392
PHLOX: SUB-COMMANDER.

461
00:24:36,434 --> 00:24:39,061
T'POL: DON'T BE FRIGHTENED.
I WON'T HURT YOU.

462
00:24:39,103 --> 00:24:40,854
PHLOX: YOU'RE DISTURBING
MY SERUM!

463
00:24:40,896 --> 00:24:42,440
OBVIOUSLY YOU NEED
TO BE SEDATED AGAIN.

464
00:24:42,522 --> 00:24:44,442
T'POL: NO MORE HYPOSPRAYS!

465
00:24:44,482 --> 00:24:45,734
[BEEPS]

466
00:24:45,776 --> 00:24:48,528
PHLOX: ONE OF US
SHOULD PROBABLY ANSWER THAT.

467
00:24:48,570 --> 00:24:51,657
I--IT COULD BE NEWS
ABOUT THE CAPTAIN.

468
00:24:51,698 --> 00:24:55,035
[BEEPS]

469
00:24:55,077 --> 00:24:56,912
THIS IS PHLOX.

470
00:24:56,954 --> 00:24:58,496
TUCKER: Anyone hungry in there?

471
00:24:58,538 --> 00:25:00,291
I brought you some supper.

472
00:25:02,376 --> 00:25:05,296
PHLOX: JUST IN THE NICK OF TIME,
COMMANDER.

473
00:25:08,382 --> 00:25:11,177
IT WOULD BE BEST
IF YOU REMAINED HERE.

474
00:25:17,683 --> 00:25:19,768
TUCKER: HOW ARE YOU
TWO HOLDING UP?

475
00:25:19,810 --> 00:25:22,188
PHLOX: WELL ENOUGH.

476
00:25:24,648 --> 00:25:26,859
HAVE YOU BEEN ABLE
TO LOCATE CAPTAIN ARCHER?

477
00:25:26,900 --> 00:25:28,819
TUCKER: WE'RE TRACKING ANOTHER
WARP SIGNATURE.

478
00:25:28,861 --> 00:25:31,238
HOPEFULLY THIS ONE'S
THE REAL THING.

479
00:25:31,280 --> 00:25:33,949
ARE THOSE THE ONES YOU WANTED?

480
00:25:33,991 --> 00:25:36,369
PHLOX: YES. THANK YOU.

481
00:25:36,410 --> 00:25:37,744
T'POL: IS THAT FOOD?

482
00:25:37,786 --> 00:25:40,414
TUCKER: YEAH.

483
00:25:40,456 --> 00:25:43,376
I HAD CHEF MAKE YOU SOME...

484
00:25:46,879 --> 00:25:48,630
IS SHE ALL RIGHT?

485
00:25:48,672 --> 00:25:51,050
PHLOX:
SHE'S DEVELOPED A SLIGHT FEVER.

486
00:25:51,091 --> 00:25:52,759
NOTHING TO BE CONCERNED ABOUT.

487
00:25:57,473 --> 00:25:58,598
[BEEPS]

488
00:25:58,640 --> 00:26:00,267
REED:
Bridge to Commander Tucker.

489
00:26:00,309 --> 00:26:01,519
TUCKER: GO AHEAD.

490
00:26:01,559 --> 00:26:03,354
REED: We're approaching
the coordinates.

491
00:26:03,396 --> 00:26:04,730
TUCKER: ON MY WAY.

492
00:26:06,065 --> 00:26:08,442
CALL IF YOU NEED ANYTHING.

493
00:26:21,080 --> 00:26:22,498
WHAT HAVE YOU GOT?

494
00:26:22,540 --> 00:26:24,041
REED: TWO MATCHING
WARP SIGNATURES,

495
00:26:24,083 --> 00:26:25,459
BOTH IN THE UPPER ATMOSPHERE.

496
00:26:25,501 --> 00:26:27,127
MORE SUBSPACE BEACONS.

497
00:26:27,169 --> 00:26:28,628
THERE IS A SHIP ON THE SURFACE.

498
00:26:28,670 --> 00:26:30,381
IT SEEMS TO HAVE SUFFERED
ENGINE DAMAGE.

499
00:26:30,423 --> 00:26:32,258
BUT IT'S NOT TELLARITE.

500
00:26:32,299 --> 00:26:34,176
TUCKER: BIO-SIGNS?
REED: ONE.

501
00:26:36,220 --> 00:26:38,013
TUCKER: OPEN A CHANNEL.

502
00:26:40,640 --> 00:26:42,184
KAGO-DARR:<i> YES?</i>

503
00:26:42,226 --> 00:26:43,894
TUCKER: SORRY TO BOTHER YOU,

504
00:26:43,936 --> 00:26:45,771
BUT WE'RE LOOKING
FOR A TELLARITE SHUTTLE.

505
00:26:45,812 --> 00:26:47,814
HAVE YOU SEEN ONE?

506
00:26:47,856 --> 00:26:49,942
KAGO-DARR:<i> HOW MUCH DID</i>
<i>THE KLINGONS OFFER YOU?</i>

507
00:26:49,983 --> 00:26:52,694
TUCKER: KLINGONS?

508
00:26:54,821 --> 00:26:56,240
TUCKER: LOOK, THERE MUST BE

509
00:26:56,282 --> 00:26:57,741
SOME SORT OF
MISUNDERSTANDING HERE.

510
00:26:57,783 --> 00:26:59,535
WE'RE LOOKING FOR OUR CAPTAIN.

511
00:26:59,577 --> 00:27:02,620
KAGO-DARR:<i> YOUR CAPTAIN,</i>
<i>HE'S GOT A PRICE ON HIS HEAD.</i>

512
00:27:02,662 --> 00:27:06,417
<i>HE'S PROBABLY HALFWAY</i>
<i>TO KLINGON SPACE BY NOW.</i>

513
00:27:10,879 --> 00:27:14,800
TUCKER: TRAVIS, HOW CLOSE ARE WE
TO KLINGON SPACE?

514
00:27:14,841 --> 00:27:16,343
TRAVIS:
LESS THAN SIX LIGHT-YEARS.

515
00:27:16,385 --> 00:27:18,220
TUCKER: IF THAT TELLARITE'S
LOOKING TO COLLECT

516
00:27:18,262 --> 00:27:19,846
SOME KIND OF REWARD,

517
00:27:19,888 --> 00:27:22,682
WE'D BETTER FIND HIM
BEFORE HE GETS THERE.

518
00:27:22,724 --> 00:27:24,477
SET A COURSE.
TAKE US BACK TO WARP.

519
00:27:24,518 --> 00:27:26,145
TRAVIS: AYE, SIR.

520
00:27:36,614 --> 00:27:38,616
GAAVRIN:
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

521
00:27:38,656 --> 00:27:40,409
SKALAAR: I NEED YOUR HELP.

522
00:27:40,451 --> 00:27:42,286
GAAVRIN:
YOU SHOULDN'T HAVE BROUGHT HIM!

523
00:27:42,328 --> 00:27:43,870
SKALAAR: YOU THINK
I WOULD'VE COME HERE

524
00:27:43,912 --> 00:27:45,372
IF I HAD A CHOICE?

525
00:27:45,414 --> 00:27:48,250
I NEED AN ANTIMATTER INJECTOR.

526
00:27:48,292 --> 00:27:50,710
GAAVRIN: AND I SUPPOSE YOU HAVE
NO WAY OF PAYING FOR IT.

527
00:27:50,752 --> 00:27:52,338
SKALAAR:
DO YOU KNOW WHO THIS IS?

528
00:27:52,379 --> 00:27:53,922
HE'S THE ONLY PRISONER

529
00:27:53,964 --> 00:27:55,799
WHO'S EVER ESCAPED
FROM RURA PENTHE.

530
00:27:55,841 --> 00:27:58,051
THE KLINGONS ARE OFFERING
A FORTUNE TO GET HIM BACK.

531
00:27:58,093 --> 00:27:59,386
TELL HIM.

532
00:28:00,804 --> 00:28:02,640
TELL HIM!

533
00:28:04,224 --> 00:28:05,934
GAAVRIN:
IF I GIVE YOU THE INJECTOR,

534
00:28:05,976 --> 00:28:08,604
YOU HAVE TO PROMISE
NEVER TO COME BACK HERE.

535
00:28:08,646 --> 00:28:10,814
SKALAAR:
OF COURSE I'M COMING BACK.

536
00:28:10,856 --> 00:28:12,774
YOU'RE GOING TO BE
MY FIRST OFFICER.

537
00:28:12,816 --> 00:28:15,528
GAAVRIN: THAT WAS YEARS AGO!
I WORK HERE NOW.

538
00:28:15,569 --> 00:28:17,279
SKALAAR:
SCRUBBING PLASMA INJECTORS?

539
00:28:17,321 --> 00:28:19,323
IS THAT HOW YOU WANT
YOUR CHILDREN TO SEE YOU?

540
00:28:19,365 --> 00:28:21,283
GAAVRIN: IT'S BETTER
THAN HUNTING CRIMINALS.

541
00:28:21,325 --> 00:28:22,951
SKALAAR: YOU THINK THAT
I ENJOY SPENDING MY TIME

542
00:28:22,993 --> 00:28:25,329
WITH VERMIN LIKE HIM?

543
00:28:25,371 --> 00:28:27,581
GAAVRIN: I HAVE WORK TO DO.

544
00:28:27,623 --> 00:28:30,584
SKALAAR: PLEASE DON'T TURN
YOUR BACK ON ME AGAIN.

545
00:28:30,626 --> 00:28:33,045
WE CAN RECLAIM THE "TEZRA."

546
00:28:34,630 --> 00:28:37,424
GAAVRIN: YOU WON'T WANT
THAT SHIP AFTER YOU SEE IT.

547
00:28:37,466 --> 00:28:40,553
SKALAAR: WHY NOT?

548
00:28:40,594 --> 00:28:43,055
GAAVRIN:
THE KLINGONS CANNIBALIZED HER.

549
00:28:43,096 --> 00:28:46,141
EVERY POWER RELAY,
EVERY CONDUIT.

550
00:28:46,183 --> 00:28:47,518
SKALAAR: THE ENGINES?

551
00:28:47,560 --> 00:28:50,312
GAAVRIN: THEY'RE GONE.

552
00:28:51,564 --> 00:28:53,691
I'LL GIVE YOU THE INJECTOR.

553
00:28:53,732 --> 00:28:57,653
BUT AFTER THAT,
I WANT YOU TO LEAVE.

554
00:29:10,457 --> 00:29:12,334
ARCHER:
WHAT DO YOU PLAN TO DO NOW?

555
00:29:12,376 --> 00:29:15,462
SKALAAR: GET THAT INJECTOR
AND INSTALL IT.

556
00:29:15,504 --> 00:29:17,339
ARCHER: AND THEN?

557
00:29:22,595 --> 00:29:24,722
I SUPPOSE YOU'LL TURN ME OVER
TO THE KLINGONS.

558
00:29:26,473 --> 00:29:28,892
I'LL BE...

559
00:29:28,934 --> 00:29:30,852
DISEMBOWELED WITH
ONE OF THOSE

560
00:29:30,894 --> 00:29:32,646
NASTY-LOOKING SWORDS OF THEIRS.

561
00:29:35,649 --> 00:29:38,860
AND YOU'LL COLLECT
YOUR 9,000 DARSEKS.

562
00:29:41,196 --> 00:29:43,532
BUT IT WON'T GET YOU
THE "TEZRA" BACK.

563
00:29:43,574 --> 00:29:45,200
SKALAAR: WHAT ARE YOU
TRYING TO SAY?

564
00:29:45,242 --> 00:29:49,371
ARCHER: THE KLINGONS TOOK
YOUR FREIGHTER, YOUR LIVELIHOOD.

565
00:29:52,082 --> 00:29:54,960
DAMAGED YOUR RELATIONSHIP
WITH YOUR BROTHER.

566
00:29:56,462 --> 00:29:58,964
AND WHAT DO YOU GET IN EXCHANGE?

567
00:29:59,005 --> 00:30:01,425
9,000 DARSEKS.

568
00:30:02,842 --> 00:30:06,346
DOESN'T SEEM LIKE
A VERY FAIR TRADE TO ME.

569
00:30:06,388 --> 00:30:08,641
SKALAAR: WHAT CHOICE DO I HAVE?

570
00:30:08,682 --> 00:30:12,018
I TOLD YOU, IF I LET YOU GO,
THEY'D KILL ME.

571
00:30:13,145 --> 00:30:14,688
ARCHER: MAYBE NOT.

572
00:30:16,064 --> 00:30:18,692
HAVE YOU EVER BEEN ABOARD
GOROTH'S SHIP?

573
00:30:20,026 --> 00:30:22,362
SKALAAR: TWICE. WHY?

574
00:30:24,990 --> 00:30:26,992
[T'POL SPEAKS VULCAN]

575
00:30:27,033 --> 00:30:28,327
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

576
00:30:28,368 --> 00:30:30,704
[REPEATS IN VULCAN]

577
00:30:32,289 --> 00:30:33,666
[REPEATS IN VULCAN]

578
00:30:33,707 --> 00:30:35,709
PHLOX: I BEG YOUR PARDON?

579
00:30:38,545 --> 00:30:40,172
T'POL: LET ME OUT.

580
00:30:40,213 --> 00:30:41,757
PHLOX: YOU KNOW I CAN'T DO THAT.

581
00:30:41,799 --> 00:30:45,051
T'POL: THE HEAT!
IT'S UNBEARABLE!

582
00:30:45,093 --> 00:30:46,679
PHLOX:
IF I LOWER THE TEMPERATURE,

583
00:30:46,720 --> 00:30:48,472
THE SERUM WILL START TO CONGEAL.

584
00:30:48,514 --> 00:30:50,474
T'POL: I DON'T WANT
YOUR SERUM! OPEN THE DOOR!

585
00:30:50,516 --> 00:30:52,351
PHLOX: I ASSURE YOU YOU'RE
GOING TO FEEL MUCH BETTER

586
00:30:52,392 --> 00:30:53,811
IN JUST A FEW MINUTES.

587
00:30:53,852 --> 00:30:55,729
T'POL: OPEN IT!

588
00:30:55,771 --> 00:30:57,981
PHLOX:
THIS WILL ONLY TAKE A MOMENT.

589
00:31:01,026 --> 00:31:03,612
YOUR BIOCHEMICAL IMBALANCE
IS GROWING WORSE.

590
00:31:03,654 --> 00:31:05,155
IF WE DON'T TREAT IT NOW,

591
00:31:05,197 --> 00:31:07,574
THE DAMAGE TO YOUR LIMBIC SYSTEM
COULD BE IRREVERSIBLE.

592
00:31:07,616 --> 00:31:10,076
YOU SAID IT YOURSELF, T'POL.
IT COULD KILL YOU!

593
00:31:10,118 --> 00:31:11,662
T'POL: STAY AWAY FROM ME.

594
00:31:11,704 --> 00:31:15,123
PHLOX: ONE INJECTION.
THAT'S ALL I ASK.

595
00:31:15,165 --> 00:31:16,750
[T'POL GRUNTS]

596
00:31:18,210 --> 00:31:20,045
[PHLOX SIGHS]

597
00:31:20,086 --> 00:31:21,672
PHLOX: VERY WELL.

598
00:31:23,757 --> 00:31:25,300
YOU'RE FREE TO GO.

599
00:31:25,342 --> 00:31:28,762
42864.
THAT'S THE LOCKING CODE.

600
00:31:28,804 --> 00:31:30,723
DENOBULAN MEDICAL ETHICS
PREVENT ME

601
00:31:30,764 --> 00:31:33,600
FROM TREATING PATIENTS
AGAINST THEIR WILL.

602
00:31:33,642 --> 00:31:36,395
42864!

603
00:31:50,242 --> 00:31:52,118
[BUZZES]

604
00:31:56,790 --> 00:31:59,000
[BUZZES]

605
00:32:00,794 --> 00:32:02,588
[T'POL GROANS]

606
00:32:45,881 --> 00:32:47,507
PHLOX: PHLOX TO THE BRIDGE.

607
00:32:47,549 --> 00:32:49,008
TUCKER: Tucker here.

608
00:32:49,050 --> 00:32:51,553
PHLOX: YOU MAY WANT
TO EVACUATE "D" DECK.

609
00:32:58,226 --> 00:33:00,604
REED: SHE'S STILL
IN THIS SECTION.

610
00:33:00,646 --> 00:33:04,190
THE DOCTOR SAYS SHE'S
IRRATIONAL, SO USE CAUTION.

611
00:33:04,232 --> 00:33:05,859
CREWMAN: YES, SIR.

612
00:33:16,161 --> 00:33:17,788
T'POL: MALCOLM!

613
00:33:21,040 --> 00:33:23,293
[T'POL BREATHING HEAVILY]

614
00:33:23,335 --> 00:33:25,086
I NEED YOUR ASSISTANCE.

615
00:33:25,128 --> 00:33:26,505
REED: WE'VE BEEN VERY WORRIED

616
00:33:26,546 --> 00:33:27,631
ABOUT YOU, SUB-COMMANDER.

617
00:33:27,673 --> 00:33:29,800
LET'S GET YOU BACK
TO THE DOCTOR.

618
00:33:29,842 --> 00:33:31,677
T'POL:
I CAN'T RETURN TO THE DOCTOR.

619
00:33:31,718 --> 00:33:33,804
HE'S REFUSING TO TREAT ME.

620
00:33:36,932 --> 00:33:38,517
HOW LONG HAS IT BEEN?

621
00:33:38,558 --> 00:33:40,602
REED: I BEG YOUR PARDON?

622
00:33:40,644 --> 00:33:43,271
T'POL: SINCE YOU'VE MATED?

623
00:33:45,524 --> 00:33:48,276
I'VE SEEN THE WAY
YOU LOOK AT ME.

624
00:33:50,320 --> 00:33:52,531
ON THE BRIDGE.

625
00:33:52,572 --> 00:33:55,701
REED: WHY DON'T WE DISCUSS
THIS IN DECON?

626
00:33:55,742 --> 00:33:59,621
T'POL: MY QUARTERS
WOULD BE MORE COMFORTABLE.

627
00:34:01,206 --> 00:34:04,083
REED:
DR. PHLOX WAS VERY INSISTENT.

628
00:34:33,196 --> 00:34:35,323
FOLLOW ME, SUB-COMMANDER.

629
00:34:38,201 --> 00:34:39,995
[T'POL SHOUTS IN VULCAN]

630
00:34:56,469 --> 00:34:58,889
SKALAAR: WELCOME!

631
00:35:03,060 --> 00:35:05,228
[BEEPING]

632
00:35:05,270 --> 00:35:08,273
GOROTH: THE EMPIRE NEVER FORGETS
ITS ENEMIES.

633
00:35:08,314 --> 00:35:10,483
[GOROTH SHOUTS IN KLINGON]

634
00:35:10,525 --> 00:35:12,694
SKALAAR: WHAT ABOUT MY PAYMENT?

635
00:35:15,655 --> 00:35:17,699
6,000 DARSEKS.

636
00:35:17,741 --> 00:35:19,659
SKALAAR: WE AGREED TO NINE.

637
00:35:19,701 --> 00:35:22,871
GOROTH: DID WE?

638
00:35:22,913 --> 00:35:26,499
ARCHER: THAT'S BLOOD MONEY,
SKALAAR. HOPE YOU ENJOY IT.

639
00:35:41,890 --> 00:35:43,016
[BEEPS]

640
00:35:43,058 --> 00:35:46,227
HOSHI: WE'RE BEING
HAILED, COMMANDER.

641
00:35:46,269 --> 00:35:48,229
HOSHI: IT'S THE TELLARITE SHIP.

642
00:35:48,271 --> 00:35:49,940
TUCKER: WHAT?

643
00:35:52,275 --> 00:35:54,069
PUT HIM THROUGH.

644
00:36:02,577 --> 00:36:04,621
[CLICK]

645
00:36:10,669 --> 00:36:12,754
[CLICKING]

646
00:36:29,729 --> 00:36:32,691
[BEEPING]

647
00:36:32,732 --> 00:36:34,192
[CLICKING]

648
00:36:34,233 --> 00:36:37,445
[ALARM]

649
00:37:14,191 --> 00:37:16,317
REED: I'VE GOT THEM.

650
00:37:16,359 --> 00:37:18,403
BEARING 226 MARK 71.

651
00:37:18,444 --> 00:37:20,113
TUCKER: SET A COURSE.

652
00:37:20,155 --> 00:37:21,740
GO TO TACTICAL ALERT.

653
00:37:26,452 --> 00:37:28,038
[DOOR OPENS]

654
00:37:47,473 --> 00:37:49,184
[BUZZES]

655
00:37:51,477 --> 00:37:54,147
[BUZZES]

656
00:38:07,660 --> 00:38:09,579
GOROTH: WHERE DO YOU THINK
YOU'LL GO, HUMAN?!

657
00:38:09,621 --> 00:38:13,125
THERE ISN'T A PLANET
WITHIN 50 LIGHT-YEARS.

658
00:38:32,060 --> 00:38:34,437
HE WON'T GET FAR.
DROP OUT OF WARP.

659
00:38:34,479 --> 00:38:35,981
OFFICER:
SHOULD I CHARGE WEAPONS?

660
00:38:36,022 --> 00:38:38,441
GOROTH: NO. I WANT HIM ALIVE.

661
00:38:43,196 --> 00:38:45,991
TRAVIS: I SEE HIM.
800,000 KILOMETERS.

662
00:38:46,032 --> 00:38:49,286
TUCKER: WHAT ABOUT THE KLINGONS?
REED: THEY'RE CLOSING IN ON HIM.

663
00:39:00,255 --> 00:39:02,507
THEY'RE CHARGING WEAPONS.

664
00:39:02,548 --> 00:39:04,843
TUCKER: RETURN FIRE!

665
00:39:04,884 --> 00:39:06,636
DEPLOY THE GRAPPLER!

666
